205
00:06:31.780 --> 00:06:36.410
Wano
Ringo

206
00:06:48.170 --> 00:06:49.430
There you are.

207
00:06:50.300 --> 00:06:54.890
You're the one who stole my sword, right?

208
00:06:56.100 --> 00:06:59.560
It is not your sword...

209
00:07:03.310 --> 00:07:08.530
The named blade Shusui has already
been returned to where it belongs.

210
00:07:08.530 --> 00:07:15.030
It's a treasure that was stolen from the grave
of the legendary samurai of Wano, Ryuma!

211
00:07:15.870 --> 00:07:17.120
I'm aware!

212
00:07:18.080 --> 00:07:20.670
Then keep quiet and turn back!

213
00:07:23.580 --> 00:07:29.260
Or I will also claim those two swords
strapped to your waist!

214
00:07:30.760 --> 00:07:32.590
A weapon collector, huh?

215
00:07:34.180 --> 00:07:36.890
What are you gonna do with all those?

216
00:07:38.890 --> 00:07:42.600
As it happens, we could do
with a bunch of weapons, too,

217
00:07:42.600 --> 00:07:44.810
so your timing's perfect.

218
00:07:47.270 --> 00:07:49.280
That collection of yours...

219
00:07:51.070 --> 00:07:53.320
I'm gonna take the whole thing!

220
00:08:01.040 --> 00:08:04.380
Not if I bring you down first, mountain bandit!

221
00:08:07.550 --> 00:08:10.340
I'm sorry if you misunderstood...

222
00:08:10.840 --> 00:08:12.340
but I'm...

223
00:08:12.880 --> 00:08:14.430
a pirate!

224
00:08:14.510 --> 00:08:21.230
Wano's Prisoner
Mining Camp in Udon

225
00:08:34.340 --> 00:08:38.580
You crack me up.

226
00:08:44.370 --> 00:08:47.750
Your Awesomeness!
He'll understand once it starts!

227
00:08:49.590 --> 00:08:53.760
He just doesn't get how rigged this game is!

228
00:08:53.760 --> 00:08:57.430
He's clueless about his odds for survival!

229
00:08:59.310 --> 00:09:01.180
You're right!

230
00:09:01.180 --> 00:09:05.480
Get ready to enter the ring, guys!

231
00:09:13.570 --> 00:09:17.540
– Deathmatch! Deathmatch! Deathmatch!
– Deathmatch! Deathmatch! Deathmatch!

232
00:09:15.660 --> 00:09:17.530
Th-There are too many of them...!

233
00:09:18.950 --> 00:09:22.240
Not to mention, we're armed to the teeth.

234
00:09:22.240 --> 00:09:23.910
No weapons for you!

235
00:09:25.620 --> 00:09:30.420
Is it sinking in that you're dead men walking?!

236
00:09:30.420 --> 00:09:33.300
– Deathmatch! Deathmatch!
– Deathmatch! Deathmatch!

237
00:09:33.300 --> 00:09:38.300
– Deathmatch! Deathmatch! Deathmatch!
– Deathmatch! Deathmatch! Deathmatch!

238
00:09:38.800 --> 00:09:43.520
Rest in peace, old man Hyo and Straw Hat...

239
00:09:44.350 --> 00:09:46.890
Lock eyes with your opponents!

240
00:09:48.270 --> 00:09:50.520
Ready...!

241
00:09:50.520 --> 00:09:52.110
Begin!

242
00:09:53.980 --> 00:09:57.030
The rest of your prisoners, watch and learn!

243
00:09:57.570 --> 00:10:00.660
This is what happens when you defy a guard!

244
00:10:21.850 --> 00:10:25.560
Who's next?! They're not
even a good warm-up!

245
00:10:28.980 --> 00:10:31.940
– Whaaat?!
– Whaaat?!

246
00:10:31.940 --> 00:10:33.940
Did he just use...?!

247
00:10:39.200 --> 00:10:41.660
So he's got conqueror's haki.

248
00:10:45.660 --> 00:10:46.700
You...

249
00:10:51.170 --> 00:10:53.630
Looks like this is gonna be interesting.

250
00:10:53.640 --> 00:10:57.420
Pleasures, enter the ring!

251
00:11:05.470 --> 00:11:08.480
Things have gotten quite rowdy
since he showed up...

252
00:11:12.100 --> 00:11:16.070
Just don't let Boss Hyogoro die.

253
00:11:20.820 --> 00:11:22.990
I'm counting on you, Luffytaro.

254
00:11:26.910 --> 00:11:29.080
A Bathhouse
Flower Capital

255
00:11:29.080 --> 00:11:30.120
It's a raid!

256
00:11:36.500 --> 00:11:40.590
That's Hawkins, a Headliner
for the Beast Pirates!

257
00:11:40.590 --> 00:11:42.510
Nobody move!

258
00:11:43.550 --> 00:11:46.680
What could you possibly
want with a bathhouse?

259
00:11:46.680 --> 00:11:49.930
Inspecting a bathhouse is ideal...

260
00:11:49.930 --> 00:11:53.350
because everyone's naked
and we can see everything.

261
00:11:54.360 --> 00:11:58.030
Drake, what are you doing? Get inside.

262
00:11:58.030 --> 00:12:02.490
I'm only tasked to take down
that Soba Mask idiot.

263
00:12:03.490 --> 00:12:06.200
You can do your own dirty work.

264
00:12:08.290 --> 00:12:13.250
What do we do, Shinobu?!
They probably know about us.

265
00:12:13.250 --> 00:12:15.210
They came for us.

266
00:12:15.210 --> 00:12:18.340
It's not fair! We're vulnerable here!

267
00:12:18.340 --> 00:12:19.760
Should we fight?

268
00:12:19.760 --> 00:12:21.720
As a last resort.

269
00:12:21.720 --> 00:12:25.760
Mature women shouldn't
draw their weapons recklessly.

270
00:12:27.140 --> 00:12:29.390
Hide behind me.

271
00:12:33.310 --> 00:12:36.440
Everyone, line up and show us your ankles!

272
00:12:36.440 --> 00:12:37.310
– What?!
– What?!

273
00:12:37.770 --> 00:12:41.990
Anyone with a reversed crescent moon
tattoo on their ankle is coming with us!

274
00:12:46.070 --> 00:12:49.580
That means getting out of the tub, too!

275
00:12:50.330 --> 00:12:53.210
I can't believe it. How does he know?!

276
00:12:53.210 --> 00:12:54.210
Search them.

277
00:12:54.210 --> 00:12:55.790
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

278
00:12:56.210 --> 00:12:58.210
Was the plan leaked?

279
00:13:08.470 --> 00:13:10.100
Someone's back there!

280
00:13:13.980 --> 00:13:15.060
Show yourself!

281
00:13:17.650 --> 00:13:20.150
Nami! I've got your back if anything happens.

282
00:13:23.190 --> 00:13:26.530
Sorry, I wasn't trying to hide!

283
00:13:26.530 --> 00:13:28.820
I'm just another patron.

284
00:13:29.280 --> 00:13:30.250
You...!

285
00:13:45.550 --> 00:13:48.670
– Dynamite!
– Oh, my! She's a national treasure!

286
00:13:50.640 --> 00:13:51.930
How devastating!

287
00:13:52.970 --> 00:13:54.890
I can't believe it!

288
00:13:56.770 --> 00:13:58.470
That's beyond powerful, Nami!

289
00:13:59.270 --> 00:14:02.190
It's her Happiness Punch!

290
00:14:02.190 --> 00:14:03.690
What...?

291
00:14:06.780 --> 00:14:09.160
Is that...? He's the guy from yesterday.

292
00:14:09.570 --> 00:14:11.370
Soba Mask!

293
00:14:12.580 --> 00:14:14.040
Na... mi...

294
00:14:14.040 --> 00:14:19.330
The shape of Nami's body was magnificent
like a mighty flowing river...

295
00:14:21.790 --> 00:14:24.210
Sanji! What's he doing here?!

296
00:14:24.210 --> 00:14:26.630
What's he wearing?! Is this a joke?!

297
00:14:26.630 --> 00:14:27.840
Drake!

298
00:14:28.510 --> 00:14:30.140
Soba Mask?!

299
00:14:30.140 --> 00:14:32.010
He was inside all along!

300
00:14:32.720 --> 00:14:34.430
Hey! Where's Soba Mask?!

301
00:14:34.430 --> 00:14:35.600
What?!

302
00:14:38.140 --> 00:14:39.310
Where–

303
00:14:44.650 --> 00:14:47.740
You should've told me that
you're shy around naked women!

304
00:14:48.450 --> 00:14:50.320
I'm not...

305
00:14:53.030 --> 00:14:57.200
Drake... you're from the North Blue, right?

306
00:14:57.200 --> 00:15:00.080
So are you... What of it?

307
00:15:01.380 --> 00:15:03.920
Then you're familiar with him, correct?

308
00:15:12.010 --> 00:15:13.850
That's Germa 66's...

309
00:15:13.850 --> 00:15:15.600
Stealth Black!

310
00:15:21.900 --> 00:15:23.400
Stop running!

311
00:15:23.400 --> 00:15:25.900
We're still searchin–

312
00:15:25.900 --> 00:15:26.860
Here's our chance!

313
00:15:28.030 --> 00:15:30.530
Go to hell, Germa 66!

314
00:15:32.450 --> 00:15:33.780
Soba Mask!

315
00:15:35.910 --> 00:15:38.370
Is it Stealth Black's transmission device?!

316
00:15:39.500 --> 00:15:41.250
Hang on tight!

317
00:15:44.590 --> 00:15:47.170
He's flying! After him!

318
00:15:49.970 --> 00:15:52.300
That's Stealth Black for you...!

319
00:15:52.300 --> 00:15:54.140
I'll get him next time!

320
00:15:55.930 --> 00:15:58.020
Sanji, care to explain?!

321
00:15:58.020 --> 00:16:00.850
It's a long story! I'll tell you later!

322
00:16:02.310 --> 00:16:04.480
Aren't you losing a lot of blood?

323
00:16:04.860 --> 00:16:07.150
I could die happy right now!

324
00:16:08.030 --> 00:16:12.030
Anyway, it's a pain that they've
caught on to the ankle tattoos!

325
00:16:12.030 --> 00:16:15.700
Yes... I wonder how they found out...

326
00:16:15.700 --> 00:16:20.200
On my way to the bathhouse,
I overheard some more bad news.

327
00:16:21.750 --> 00:16:23.500
Bepo's group was captured!

328
00:16:23.500 --> 00:16:24.370
– What?
– What?

329
00:16:25.040 --> 00:16:30.920
It seems the Beast Pirates
are using Traf's crew as bait.

330
00:16:30.920 --> 00:16:33.340
I'm sure he'll want to rescue them.

331
00:16:33.340 --> 00:16:35.340
They're his crew, after all.

332
00:16:37.760 --> 00:16:39.810
We can't let him.

333
00:16:39.810 --> 00:16:43.380
The Flower Capital would fall into chaos!

334
00:16:43.380 --> 00:16:46.690
And you were wasting time
doing what exactly?

335
00:16:56.700 --> 00:16:59.990
I wanna have some oshiruko already.

336
00:16:59.990 --> 00:17:04.160
Hey, haven't we reached that Udon place yet?

337
00:17:04.540 --> 00:17:06.790
Chopperemon!

338
00:17:06.790 --> 00:17:09.590
I'm starving.

339
00:17:09.590 --> 00:17:12.260
Don't drool when you look at me!

340
00:17:12.920 --> 00:17:16.260
It won't be long now, Olin!

341
00:17:16.260 --> 00:17:20.390
When we get to Udon,
we'll save Big Bro Luffy.

342
00:17:20.390 --> 00:17:22.850
And then...

343
00:17:22.850 --> 00:17:25.570
we'll have...

344
00:17:25.570 --> 00:17:28.770
some oshiruko soup!

345
00:17:30.690 --> 00:17:33.740
You like it too, Otama?

346
00:17:33.740 --> 00:17:36.820
Yup, I love it!

347
00:17:37.240 --> 00:17:42.450
Miss Otsuru treated me
to some for my birthday!

348
00:17:43.330 --> 00:17:47.460
My mouth slowly filled with
the sweetness of the red-bean paste...

349
00:17:47.460 --> 00:17:52.000
It truly tickled my taste buds.

350
00:17:52.000 --> 00:17:54.300
I know!

351
00:17:54.300 --> 00:17:57.630
Red-bean paste is the best!

352
00:17:57.630 --> 00:18:00.050
Yes! Yes! Absolutely!

353
00:18:00.050 --> 00:18:01.140
Uh-huh! Uh-huh!

354
00:18:01.510 --> 00:18:04.810
Red-bean paste! And mochi!

355
00:18:04.810 --> 00:18:10.440
It was the softest and tastiest
thing I've ever had!

356
00:18:10.440 --> 00:18:12.320
I know, I know!

357
00:18:12.900 --> 00:18:18.030
Mochi shines just like a frog's eyeball!

358
00:18:18.030 --> 00:18:19.530
What?!

359
00:18:19.530 --> 00:18:21.070
A frog's eyeball?

360
00:18:23.540 --> 00:18:26.790
Olin, that's a little freaky.

361
00:18:26.790 --> 00:18:28.670
Oh, really?

362
00:18:28.670 --> 00:18:30.790
Well, when I think about it...

363
00:18:32.420 --> 00:18:35.510
I can't help drooling.

364
00:18:35.510 --> 00:18:37.050
I'm not edible!

365
00:18:39.430 --> 00:18:42.300
I really can't wait to have some oshiruko!

366
00:18:42.300 --> 00:18:45.970
They are getting quite excited
about the oshiruko.

367
00:18:45.970 --> 00:18:47.770
It's no good.

368
00:18:49.650 --> 00:18:51.520
What should I do?

369
00:18:53.190 --> 00:18:55.440
When she learns there is no oshiruko,

370
00:18:55.440 --> 00:18:58.070
the shock might restore her memories,

371
00:18:58.070 --> 00:19:00.700
and she'll be Big Mom again!

372
00:19:00.700 --> 00:19:04.580
Straw Hat!

373
00:19:05.790 --> 00:19:09.370
Instead of saving Luffy,
we'd be putting him in harm's way!

374
00:19:10.500 --> 00:19:11.630
What should I do?!

375
00:19:12.290 --> 00:19:15.300
What should I do?!
What am I supposed to do?!

376
00:19:26.430 --> 00:19:28.480
Get some more soup!

377
00:19:28.480 --> 00:19:29.150
Yes, sir!

378
00:20:07.560 --> 00:20:09.770
Luffytaro wins!

379
00:20:10.560 --> 00:20:12.520
You did it, Luffytaro!

380
00:20:12.520 --> 00:20:16.400
Incredible! You beat all the Pleasures...!

381
00:20:21.650 --> 00:20:22.450
That's not it.

382
00:20:22.450 --> 00:20:26.280
What's not it? You won again!

383
00:20:26.280 --> 00:20:31.080
Well, Rayleigh did it so easily.

384
00:20:31.080 --> 00:20:32.080
Rayleigh?

385
00:20:32.080 --> 00:20:33.460
Yeah.

386
00:20:35.830 --> 00:20:36.960
Luffy...

387
00:20:37.460 --> 00:20:42.720
imagine that using armament haki
is like wearing invisible armor.

388
00:20:43.880 --> 00:20:47.720
Back then, Rayleigh sent that elephant flying without touching it.

389
00:20:51.310 --> 00:20:56.900
The first time he showed me haki,
it was really advanced.

390
00:20:57.480 --> 00:20:59.400
If only I could do that...!

391
00:20:59.400 --> 00:21:02.030
We're getting nowhere with this!

392
00:21:02.030 --> 00:21:05.410
If you lemme at 'em, we'd wrap up
the execution in no time!

393
00:21:08.700 --> 00:21:13.960
You don't get the appeal of the Sumo Inferno!

394
00:21:14.870 --> 00:21:15.960
Look,

395
00:21:15.960 --> 00:21:22.760
fights are most engaging when
they're given time and numbers.

396
00:21:22.760 --> 00:21:29.100
It'll slowly sap his spirit and energy until
he succumbs to a miserable death.

397
00:21:29.810 --> 00:21:32.430
"We'd wrap up the execution in no time"?!

398
00:21:32.890 --> 00:21:35.560
Don't be so dense.

399
00:21:35.560 --> 00:21:39.230
That's not exciting at all!

400
00:21:39.230 --> 00:21:41.110
Seconds please!

401
00:21:41.110 --> 00:21:44.650
Again?! You've already had
so much red-bean soup!

402
00:21:44.650 --> 00:21:48.910
Screw you! Red-bean soup
is like oxygen to me!

403
00:21:48.910 --> 00:21:50.910
Here you go.

404
00:21:51.700 --> 00:21:54.000
No one else can have any!

405
00:21:54.000 --> 00:21:57.670
It's my oshiruko because it's my favorite!

406
00:21:57.670 --> 00:22:00.460
It's my soup!

407
00:22:05.260 --> 00:22:10.350
Send my opponent flying
as if I'm wearing invisible armor!

408
00:22:10.350 --> 00:22:13.850
Sir Straw Hat, what are you...?

409
00:22:14.930 --> 00:22:16.180
Alright!

410
00:22:16.770 --> 00:22:19.440
I wanna practice! Bring it on!

411
00:22:25.240 --> 00:22:27.240
I met Ryuma.

412
00:22:29.740 --> 00:22:32.780
Don't lie to me!

413
00:22:39.790 --> 00:22:41.920
You met Ryuma?!

414
00:22:43.670 --> 00:22:47.220
Do you expect me to believe such drivel?!

415
00:22:47.220 --> 00:22:51.220
Well, his soul belonged to
someone else I know.

416
00:22:51.220 --> 00:22:53.720
Quit talking gibberish!

417
00:22:54.930 --> 00:22:58.560
How could you know Ryuma?!

418
00:22:58.560 --> 00:23:04.440
Ryuma was a great swordsman
capable of besting any opponent in an instant!

419
00:23:05.940 --> 00:23:10.450
You have no clue how valuable
the named blade Shusui is!

420
00:23:13.950 --> 00:23:18.290
Shusui is Wano's sacred treasure!
It belongs to Ryuma!

421
00:23:23.080 --> 00:23:26.250
Long ago, when the outside world

422
00:23:26.250 --> 00:23:29.800
considered Wano to be a land of gold...

423
00:23:29.800 --> 00:23:32.720
Gold? What are you talking about?

424
00:23:32.800 --> 00:23:34.430
Wide open!

425
00:23:38.350 --> 00:23:42.150
Pirates all over the world craved our gold.

426
00:23:42.600 --> 00:23:46.650
Nobles sought to rule Wano, this land of gold!

427
00:23:48.610 --> 00:23:54.120
But one man showed those foreign invaders
just how formidable he was...

428
00:23:55.280 --> 00:23:59.450
and etched Wano's samurai
deep in their minds!

429
00:24:01.250 --> 00:24:04.790
That is the kind of man Ryuma was.

430
00:24:07.630 --> 00:24:11.090
There are countless legends about
his feats as a swordsman.

431
00:24:11.090 --> 00:24:12.260
For instance...

432
00:24:15.550 --> 00:24:19.850
it is said that he once slew a dragon
that was flying over the capital!

433
00:24:21.180 --> 00:24:24.990
After his death, honored as
Wano's God of the Blade,

434
00:24:24.990 --> 00:24:28.820
he was laid to rest in a temple
with the named blade Shusui.

435
00:24:28.820 --> 00:24:32.740
Shusui is a national treasure!

436
00:24:44.040 --> 00:24:47.630
Okay. I get it.

437
00:24:51.550 --> 00:24:55.760
But you missed the part
where I'm supposed to care!

438
00:24:57.180 --> 00:25:00.220
I'm gonna take back Shusui!

439
00:25:00.220 --> 00:25:03.060
Two swords just doesn't feel right to me.

440
00:25:05.350 --> 00:25:08.360
Is that not an overestimation
of your worthiness?

441
00:25:09.400 --> 00:25:11.780
Shusui is a black blade!

442
00:25:11.780 --> 00:25:16.740
In other words, it was forged
through the battles that Ryuma fought!

443
00:25:18.070 --> 00:25:23.830
I was merely ascertaining whether you were
a spineless whelp with no true stake to the blade!

444
00:25:24.540 --> 00:25:25.710
"Forged"?

445
00:25:26.920 --> 00:25:29.710
Oh, yeah, I was wondering about that...

446
00:25:34.050 --> 00:25:36.470
Help!

447
00:25:37.470 --> 00:25:38.930
Wide open!

448
00:25:41.720 --> 00:25:43.600
You bastard...!

449
00:25:44.730 --> 00:25:47.770
Stop trying to catch me
when my guard is down!

450
00:25:47.770 --> 00:25:53.030
Finding an opening is essential in a fight
to the death! That's all I've been doing!

451
00:25:56.240 --> 00:26:00.120
Somebody, help! Someone is trying to kill us!

452
00:26:00.120 --> 00:26:02.120
Ah! There's a samurai!

453
00:26:02.120 --> 00:26:05.710
Hey! Help us!

454
00:26:06.920 --> 00:26:10.840
Are they serious or just
fooling around? I can't tell!

455
00:26:12.550 --> 00:26:16.390
Swordsmen, please help!

456
00:26:16.390 --> 00:26:18.220
Hmm? Blood?

457
00:26:19.010 --> 00:26:21.430
I guess they're not joking.

458
00:26:50.250 --> 00:26:52.340
Hold it right there!

459
00:26:52.340 --> 00:26:55.090
Wide open!

460
00:27:01.050 --> 00:27:03.260
Can't you wait?!

461
00:27:07.270 --> 00:27:09.520
Hey, take a hint!

462
00:27:09.520 --> 00:27:13.360
Our duel is not over!

463
